DIGEST
SB 508 Original 2026 Regular Session Seabaugh
Present law provides that an insurance contract issued in Louisiana may limit the right of
action against the insurer to a period of not less than 24 months from the date of the
inception of a loss.
Proposed law retains present law.
Proposed law provides that any payment made by the insurer pursuant to the term of its
contract will not serve as an acknowledgment of a debt or otherwise interrupt the
prescriptive period.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 22:868(B))
